---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const creds = [
  { label: 'Day role', value: 'AI Automation Engineer — PerformanceX & Digital Authority Partners' },
  { label: 'Stack', value: 'Anthropic Claude SDK, Modal, Supabase, n8n, Python, TypeScript' },
  { label: 'Base', value: 'Cape Town, South Africa (SAST, UTC+2)' },
  { label: 'Next certs', value: 'CKA, Terraform Associate, AI-102' },
];
---

<Layout
  title="About — Custos"
  description="Tristan de Kock. AI Automation Engineer building sovereign, POPIA-compliant AI architecture for SA regulated industries."
>
  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="grid-bg">
    <div class="wrap" style="padding: 5rem 1.5rem 3rem;">
      <p class="label" style="margin: 0 0 1.5rem;"><span class="label-accent">About</span> &nbsp;//&nbsp; the person and the venture</p>
      <h1 class="h-display" style="font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem); max-width: 16ch;">Tristan de Kock</h1>
      <p class="lead" style="margin: 1.75rem 0 0; max-width: 54ch;">
        AI Automation Engineer in Cape Town, building production agentic systems by day and the architecture for sovereign AI in SA regulated industries through Custos.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="wrap" style="padding: 2rem 1.5rem;">
    <div class="grid-about">

      <!-- Narrative -->
      <div class="prose" style="max-width: none;">
        <p>
          By day I build production agentic systems and LLM pipelines at PerformanceX and Digital Authority Partners. Custos is the practice I am building around a specific problem: South African enterprises in regulated industries need to deploy production AI on sovereign infrastructure, and most do not yet have the architectural depth, or a trustworthy local partner, to do it correctly.
        </p>

        <h2>The problem Custos exists for</h2>
        <p>
          POPIA Section 72 restricts cross-border transfers of personal information. For health data, financial data, and biometrics, the default cloud AI pattern (a US-controlled model routed through offshore data centres) creates real compliance obligations most teams have not addressed. Cassava AI Factory changed the infrastructure equation in October 2025. The architecture problem is what is left to solve, and it is the work I want to do.
        </p>

        <h2>What I'm doing now</h2>
        <p>
          Reading POPIA end to end, building production RAG pipelines over compliance documents, benchmarking vLLM on rented H100s, and writing about what I learn. The writing is public on purpose: this field rewards demonstrated depth over claimed expertise.
        </p>

        <h2>The venture, honestly</h2>
        <p>
          Custos is not yet a registered company. I am validating demand before formalising the business, which is deliberate. The path I am building toward is Cassava Cloud Partner status as a systems integrator, with real SA case studies as proof. The first engagement on offer is a <strong>POPIA AI Readiness Assessment</strong>.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you are a CIO, CRO, or Head of Data at a SA medical aid, bank, or insurer, and "where does our AI data live?" does not have a clean answer yet, that is the conversation I want. 25 minutes, no pitch.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Spec sidebar -->
      <aside style="position: sticky; top: 84px;">
        <div style="border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 10px; background: var(--bg-surface); padding: 1.75rem;">
          <p class="label" style="margin: 0 0 1.25rem;">Profile</p>
          <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.1rem;">
            {creds.map((c) => (
              <div>
                <p style="margin: 0 0 0.25rem; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.7rem; color: var(--accent); letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase;">{c.label}</p>
                <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text); line-height: 1.5;">{c.value}</p>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
          <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/tristandekock" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="display: block; text-align: center; margin-top: 1.75rem; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--accent); border: 1px solid rgba(34,211,238,0.3); padding: 0.6rem; border-radius: 6px;">
            Connect on LinkedIn &rarr;
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
